Use Loop Function to Create Multiple WordClouds and Conduct Text Comparison of Major Media Houses¶

By Joyce Jiang | Code by Joyce¶

Declare: My code is adapted from Duong Vu's tutorial on DataCamp "Generating WordClouds in Python", you can check it out at https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/wordcloud-python. There's an unsolved problem in the discussion section of this tutorial. I solved this problem (converting a 3-D shape photo to 2-D to mask it) by using a function to convert the 3-D photo to black and white.

I found this tutorial really intuitive for someone like me who has never done WordClouds before! It does not only have step-by-step instuction but also uses the mask function to show some creative data visualizations. I added some loop function to export wordcloud multiples time for multiple datasets.

Thanks Shaumik for explaining in a digestible way for me to understand fully how WordCloud and stopword work. This script is published for study and research exploration purpose only, and it would not be used for any commercial purpose.

Text cleaning for WordCloud and use a loop function to export all wordcloud graphs. With this you'll be able to compare the frequent words used by different media houses¶

I applied two stopwords list to the wordcloud because even if after I added some words to the first one, they still showed up in the final wordcloud. There are minor differeces in each format of the word, such as capitialization, containing space and dot, etc.

In [9]:
#Text cleaning for WordCloud

dfs =[df1,df2,df3,df4,df5,df6,df7,df8,df9,df10,df11,df12,df13,df14,df15,df16,df17,df18,df19,df20]
for df in dfs:
    
    # Start with one review:
    #text1 = df1.Post[0]
    text = " ".join(post for post in df.Post)
    print ("There are {} words in the combination of all review".format(len(text))+str(df.Username[0]))
    
    re.sub(r'''(?i)\b((?:https?://|www\d{0,3}[.]|[a-z0-9.\-]+[.][a-z]{2,4}/)(?:[^\s()<>]+|\(([^\s()<>]+|(\([^\s()<>]+\)))*\))+(?:\(([^\s()<>]+|(\([^\s()<>]+\)))*\)|[^\s`!()\[\]{};:'".,<>?]))''', " ", text)
    
    all_stopwords_gensim = STOPWORDS.union(set(
        ['https','chimpreport','com', 'COVID19', 'covid','ChimpReportsNews','News','Coronavirus','chimpreports com','By',
         'coronavirus','chimpreports','UgandaNews','Uganda','Featured','chimpreports','uganda','Ugandan','COVID','www',
         'bigeye','bigeye ug','bitly','bit ly','com','co ug','COVID','coronavirus','David Isabirye','Details','nilepost',
         'Details bit','Details','How','https','independent co','It','Live','live','MonitorUpdates','NilePostNews','nilepost','nilepost co',
         'NBSUpdates','NTVNews','ntv','co','Our','Reporter','Our reporter','reporter','PMLDailyNews','redpepper co','redpepper','site','SoftPowerNews','SoftPowerNews',
         'The','softpower ug','story','bit','story nilepost','SqoopUpdates','The','This','THE INDEPENDENT','INDEPENDENT','The Independent','Independent',
         'UPDATE','update','VisionUpdates','words','words www','WWW','www','www.independent','www.softpower','www ugandaradionetwork','We','words','Luganda','ba',
         'bya','eri','ku','nti','ne','nga','mu','omu','wa','co.ug','co  ug','zionly io','zionly.io']))

    #all_stopwords_gensim = STOPWORDS.union(set(
     #   ['https','com','News','www','The','WWW']))
    
    text_tokens1 = word_tokenize(text)
    tokens_without_sw1 = [word for word in text_tokens1 if not word in all_stopwords_gensim]
    filtered_sentence = (" ").join(tokens_without_sw1)
    
    # Create stopword list
    stopwords = set(STOPWORDS)
    stopwords.update(['https', 'chimpreport', 'com', 'COVID19', 'covid','ChimpReportsNews','chimpreports','UgandaNews','https','chimpreport','com', 'COVID19', 'covid','ChimpReportsNews','News','Coronavirus','chimpreports com','By',
         'coronavirus','chimpreports','UgandaNews','Uganda','Featured','chimpreports','uganda','Ugandan','COVID','www',
         'bigeye','bigeye.ug','bitly','bit ly','com','co ug','COVID','coronavirus','David Isabirye','Details','nilepost',
         'Details bit','Details','How','https','independent co','It','Live','live','MonitorUpdates','NilePostNews','nilepost','nilepost co',
         'NBSUpdates','NTVNews','ntv','co','Our','Reporter','Our reporter','reporter','PMLDailyNews','redpepper co','redpepper','site','SoftPowerNews','SoftPowerNews',
         'The','softpower ug','story','bit','story nilepost','SqoopUpdates','The','This','THE INDEPENDENT','INDEPENDENT','The Independent','Independent',
         'UPDATE','update','VisionUpdates','words','words www','WWW','www','www.independent','www.softpower','www ugandaradionetwork','We','words','Luganda','ba',
         'bya','eri','ku','nti','ne','nga','mu','omu','wa','co.ug','co  ug','zionly io'])
    
    # Create and generate a word cloud image:
    wordcloud = WordCloud(max_font_size=50, max_words=100, background_color="white",stopwords=stopwords).generate(filtered_sentence)
    
    # Display the generated image:
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.show()
    #plt.savefig()
    wordcloud.to_file("Output/WordCloud/FB_Covid/"+str(df.Username[0])+"_Facebook_COVIDPost.png")

In [8]:
def transform_format(val):
    if val == 0:
        return 255
    else:
        return val
In [9]:
#transformed_mask = np.ndarray((mask.shape[0],mask.shape[1]), np.int32)
transformed_mask = np.ndarray((grey_mask.shape[0],grey_mask.shape[1]), np.int32)

for i in range(len(grey_mask)):
    transformed_mask[i] = list(map(transform_format, grey_mask[i]))
